OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780560333
OL,3,C'Maybe there is a change coming': On
OL,4,Cthe ground in Makerfield
OL,6,FSimon has worked as a milkman for over
OL,7,F20 years, delivering across the
OL,8,Fcollection of towns and villages on
OL,9,Fthe outskirts of Wigan that have
OL,10,Fbecome known ` in political terms ` as
OL,11,Fthe constituency of Makerfield.
OL,13,FA collection of towns and villages
OL,14,Fwhich have found themselves at the
OL,15,Fepicentre of a political storm.
OL,17,FIn just over two weeks, Makerfield ` a
OL,18,Fcentury-long Labour stronghold - could
OL,19,Fbe set to ultimately decide who runs
OL,20,FBritain.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780560333
OL,3,C'Maybe there is a change coming': On
OL,4,Cthe ground in Makerfield
OL,6,FIf he wins the by-election and becomes
OL,7,Fan MP, Greater Manchester mayor and
OL,8,FLabour's candidate Andy Burnham is
OL,9,Fpoised to launch a leadership
OL,10,Fchallenge to Keir Starmer.
OL,12,FIf he loses, the question for Labour
OL,13,Fbecomes existential. If Burnham can't
OL,14,Fbeat Reform UK, who can?
OL,16,FSimon was born and raised in Hindley,
OL,17,Fa village on the eastern edge of the
OL,18,Fconstituency. It's an area he knows
OL,19,Fwell.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780560333
OL,3,C'Maybe there is a change coming': On
OL,4,Cthe ground in Makerfield
OL,6,F"It's a working-class area, close
OL,7,Fknit, people look after each other,"
OL,8,Fhe told us.
OL,10,FBut, for him, it feels like something
OL,11,Fhas been lost.
OL,13,F"Growing up, I felt it was great, as
OL,14,Fin Great Britain, to live here and
OL,15,FI've felt that we've gradually lost
OL,16,Fthe great and I'd like to get the
OL,17,Fgreat back into Great Britain, and I
OL,18,Fdon't know how we do that," he said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@dO]uD@AOUzD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/22
