OL,3,C'Maybe there is a change coming': On
OL,4,Cthe ground in Makerfield
OL,6,FSimon's routine runs from night to day
OL,7,F` starting at 10pm and finishing at
OL,8,F7am. From there, he rushes home to
OL,9,Fdrop his three kids at school.
OL,11,F"The youngest is four years of age,"
OL,12,Fhe told us. There isn't much time for
OL,13,Fsleep.
OL,15,FAn honest night's work isn't
OL,16,Fdelivering the change he had hoped for.
OL,26,@sD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780560333
OL,3,C'Maybe there is a change coming': On
OL,4,Cthe ground in Makerfield
OL,6,F"It's just about enough," he said of
OL,7,Fthe family's income. "My wife works
OL,8,Fand I work. And it's just about
OL,9,Fenough. I can't have anything really
OL,10,Fextravagant. We manage to look after
OL,11,Four children and have a good time. But
OL,12,Fit's getting harder and harder as the
OL,13,Fyears go on. Definitely."
OL,15,FAnd, when he thinks about politics, he
OL,16,Fwants things to be different.
OL,18,F"Labour Labour Labour - that's all
OL,19,Fit's ever been, " he said. "Maybe
OL,20,Fthere is a change coming."
OL,26,@uD@YO]zD@AOU|D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
