OL,3,C'Maybe there is a change coming': On
OL,4,Cthe ground in Makerfield
OL,6,FHe insists he isn't looking at the
OL,7,Fpast through rose-tinted glasses.
OL,9,F"I grew up, we didn't have anything,"
OL,10,Fhe told us. "We made do. We never
OL,11,Fstarved. We weren't in poverty. We had
OL,12,Fclothes, we had shoe, we was housed.
OL,13,FAll the families used to muck in."
OL,15,FLiam and Lewis took a mid-morning
OL,16,Fbreak to pick up a couple of drinks a
OL,17,Ffew doors down.
OL,19,FWe went with them to Shak's
OL,20,Fnewsagents, at the heart of Ashton
OL,21,Ftown centre.
OL,26,@qD@AOUuD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/22
